Open source code signing request for ebook_viewer

Hello SignPath Foundation team,

I would like to request open source code signing support for our public Windows project.

Project name:
ebook_viewer

Repository URL:
https://github.com/spvog1213/ebook-viewer-oss/

License:
ISC

Project description:
ebook_viewer is an open source Windows desktop application built with Electron and distributed as ebook_viewer.exe for textbook viewing from a public source repository.

Primary signing target:
- ebook_viewer.exe

Additional information:
- The project is publicly available on GitHub.
- Source code, release information, and build-related documents are published in the repository.
- We have prepared a code signing policy document for the project.
- The project is intended for Windows distribution.
- The project uses GitHub Actions as its build system.

Release page:
https://github.com/spvog1213/ebook-viewer-oss/releases/tag/v1.0.0

Code signing policy:
https://github.com/spvog1213/ebook-viewer-oss/blob/main/CODE_SIGNING_POLICY.md

Please let me know if you need any additional information or changes to meet the SignPath Foundation requirements.

Best regards,
